Usage: setMessageLimit [-help] <numberToLimit> [<prefix [ID1, ID2, ...]>]

-help                        # Prints out the command usage
<numberToLimit>              # Limits error and warning messages to a specified
                             # number per unique ID. Any occurrences beyond the
                             # limit are suppressed. The default limit is 20
                             # per message ID. The default limit is applicable
                             # only for ERROR* and WARNING* messages; there is
                             # no default limit for verify*, check* and INFO*
                             # messages. (int, required)
<prefix [ID1, ID2, ...]>     # Limits error and warning messages to a specified
                             # number per unique ID of specified prefix.
                             # (string, optional)